				<td colspan="2"><span>50   Verses of Victory 
<br />
Attack Speed by 30%; Increase Agility by 30; Increase AC by 15; Increase Strength by 30;  Group Buff Singing 
<br />

<br />
57   McVaxius' Rousing Rondo 
<br />
Attack Speed by 21(L57) to 23(L65)% ; Strength by 20(L57) by 22(L65); Increase Attack by 13(L57) to 15(L65); Damage Shield by 8;  
<br />

<br />
When I have group with at least 2 other melees, I typically sing replenishment, vah shir and Rondo. I tend to stick to a 3-song twist, pulling with OOS and adding in snare/slow if required.
<br />

<br />
However I hear a lot of people seem to like VoV more - given that haste isn't an issue (I have epic, lucky ol' me!), which would you prefer? I like Rondo for the extra DPS it adds via both atk and DS, but should I use VoV instead?
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
